Desmoplastic fibroma of the maxillary sinus. Report of a case and review of the literature.
 A desmoplastic fibroma of the maxillary sinus is reported in a 15-year-old boy.
 Desmoplastic fibroma is a rare benign tumor in the maxillofacial region.
 The features of this case and of 49 previously described lesions are analyzed and discussed.
